    Summary Bootstrap

    summary.bootstrap.Rd

    This summary.bootstrap function is a method of the basic summary function. It will print a summary regarding the bootstrap class generated by the Bootstrap function. The returned values will be of class summary.bootstrap.

    # S3 method for bootstrap
summary(x, level, digits, ...)

    Arguments

    x

    is the output-list returned from the Bootstrap function

    level

    represent the confidence level of 1-alpha. By default level = 0.95

    digits

    are the decimals points desired in the printed output. By default digits = 2

    ...

    other parameters for the 'summary.bootstrap' function

    Value

    A print of the main summary information from the Bootstrap function. It also return a list composed as follow:

    summary

    Will return a list composed of the basic summary function output applied on the theta_star output

    CI

    It will return a list with the lower and upper limit of the confidence interval

    sto

    The theta_hat from the Bootstrap function

    coerced_to_a_vector

    Returning a True or Flase regarding the initial sample if it was coerced to a vector during the usage of Bootstrap function

    level

    Represent the confidence level of 1-alpha called as a parameter

    stat

    Return the name of the statistic used thruough the Bootstrap function

    B

    Number of bootrsapped samples thourgh the Bootstrap function

    Author

    Group-E

    Examples

    boot <- Bootstrap(rnorm(100), statistic = var)
summary(boot, level = 0.90)
#> Non-parametric bootstrap for 'var'
#> Number of bootstrap replicates: 1000 
#> 
#> Statistic on the sample 'x': var(x)=0.78
#> 
#> Confidence interval at the 90%-level:
#> 0.62 0.95 
#> 
#> Bootstrap estimates:
#>    Min. 1st Qu.  Median    Mean 3rd Qu.    Max. 
#>    0.46    0.71    0.77    0.78    0.84    1.15
